     <div type="poem">
   <pb facs="7"/>
   <head>Incouragement to the Booke.</head>
   <lg>
      <l>Goe on, feare none; goe too and doubt not:</l>
      <l>Some fooles make Rules, for the wise to flout at.</l>
   </lg>
   <lg>
      <l>But wise haue eyes, and wit with all,</l>
      <l>To iudge right at first sight, if the worst fall.</l>
   </lg>
   <lg>
      <l>On then, right men, vvill rightly fauor.</l>
      <l>VVhose vvit, iudging it, vvill not vvauor.</l>
   </lg>
   <lg>
      <l>But fooles haue tooles sharpe in season,</l>
      <l>To vvound and confound vvithout reason.</l>
   </lg>
</div>
